In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims August 16 through August 22, 2020, as National Employer Support of the Guard and Reserve Week. He honors the employers who hire and support the National Guard and Reserve service members, recognizing their vital role in national defense. The article highlights the importance of these citizen warriors in various sectors of the economy and their contributions to the Joint Force in uniform. It also acknowledges their courageous efforts during the COVID-19 pandemic, where they have served on the front lines and supported medical staff, distributed food, and provided medical equipment and supplies. The President calls on all Americans, as well as state and local officials and military commanders, to express gratitude and observe the week with appropriate ceremonies and activities.